hren, von Unterwerfung und Lust steht, untersucht die Repräsentation von Minoritäten in Fassbinders filmischem und dramatischem Werk aus interdisziplinärer Perspektive.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMinorities in motion picturesvCongresses. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGermanyvCongresses. 0aOutsiders in motion picturesvCongresses. 4aExklusion. 4aFassbinder. 4aLiteratur. 4aMedien. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMinorität. 4aPrekarität. 4aSoziale Ungleichheit. 4aTheater. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aLiterature.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.  aSocial Inequality.  aTheatre.1 aButte, Maren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColin, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColin, Nicole, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEzli, Özkan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGradinari, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeisterhagen, Tilman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJun, Uwe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLayne, Priscilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiebrand, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoore, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRauer, Valentin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRenner, Rolf G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRöttger, Kati, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchössler, Franziska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchößler, Franziska, eeditor.4edt4ht